description.narrative: Access to quality learning for mainstream and marginalised groups of out-of-school, non-citizen and indigenous children have been addressed through strengthened partnerships with the Ministry of Education (MOE) and other key stakeholders. UNICEF has engaged in high-level policy dialogues, supported with systemic capacity building, data generation and data analysis, as well as technical input on reopening of schools especially during COVID-19. The progress made in the year so far is attributable to a sustained, strategic, multi-pronged approach in advocacy, evidence generation and innovative programming. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
